shared_text:
Siouxland Freedom Park
September 10 at 8:27 AM ·

Due to Weather ----- On Friday, September 11, 2020 at 7:00 p.m. a 9/11 Remembrance Ceremony will be held at the Dakota City Fire Department hall, instead of Siouxland Freedom Park. The service is held to honor and remember the victims of the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks on the United States.

A dignified Retirement and Disposal Ceremony for old and damaged American flags will be held at a later time.

Due to COVID, social distancing will be practiced. They also encourage everyone to wear masks.

Event organizers include American Legion VFW Posts, Fire and Rescue Departments from the surrounding Tri-State area and the Dakota County Sheriff’s Department, and the South Sioux City Police Department.

The public is encouraged to attend.

shared_text:
Covington Elementary
August 17 at 1:48 PM ·

Happy faces with ketchup when Mrs. Dandurand gets to put it on the sandwiches 😊!

We have made several changes to our day including our lunch procedures. We’ve put marketings on the floor and through the food line to encourage to remind students to keep space between themselves. This year we also have five separate lunch times so that each grade can lunch while spaced out in the lunchroom and only sitting on one side of the lunch table. Students do wear their face covering through the lunch line. Once seated, students have a lanyard they wear to clip their face covering onto while they eat￼￼￼￼. Students then put their face coverings back on as they return their trays and head outside for recess through the hallways. Once outside, while playing, students are allowed a face covering break, students keep their face covering clipped onto the lanyard while they are at play.

Responding to the Census
The 2020 Census is happening now. You can complete your questionnaire online at 2020census.gov, by phone at 844-330-2020 (English) or 844-469-2020 (Spanish), or by mail.

Data Privacy and Confidentiality
The Census Bureau is bound by Title 13 of the U.S. Code to keep your information confidential. The answers you provide are used only to produce statistics. Violating Title 13 is a federal crime, punishable by prison time and/or a fine of up to $250,000.

Questions Asked on the Form
The 2020 Census is easy. You will answer a simple questionnaire about yourself and everyone who was living with you on April 1, 2020.

Dakota City Elementary
August 12 at 5:35 PM ·

Tomorrow is our first day of school for the 2020-2021 school year, and we are so excited to see everyone!

Just a few reminders about our changes in morning drop off...

Students should not be dropped off before 7:45am, as there will not be supervision prior to that time.

Kindergarten: line up by Doors 8 & 9
1st & 2nd Grades: line up by Door 7
3rd Grade: line up by Door 1
4th & 5th Grades: line up by Door 6

Staff will hand out masks to students beginning at 7:45am. Students can wear a mask from home if they would like.

Students will exit those same doors at the end of the school day.

Tomorrow, we dismiss at noon. Breakfast and lunch will be served. Breakfast is free for all students. Friday is a normal school day from 8:00-3:05.

post_text: The first day of school for 6th grade students is Thursday, August 13 th . We will have a 12:00 PM dismissal time, breakfast and lunch will be served. The first full day for all Middle School Students is Friday, August 14th. Please remember that the regular Middle School schedule is from 8:05 AM and ends at 3:25 PM Tuesday through Friday. Our Middle School will be dismissing every Monday at 2:25 PM to allow teachers time to work together to monitor student growth on Nebraska standards, to review data and collaborate between grade levels.

South Sioux City Police Department
August 10 at 8:43 AM ·

The South Sioux City Police Department will be out in force for three weeks looking for drinking and/or impaired drivers. The enforcement effort is titled, “Drive Sober or Get Pulled Over!” The South Sioux City Police Department will be putting extra patrols out on the streets targeting drunk and impaired drivers. We will begin our enforcement efforts the evening of August 21st 2020 and run through September 7th 2020. Funding for this project is in the form of a mini-grant applied for and awarded by the Nebraska Department of Roads and Highway Safety. Please Remember to “DRIVE SOBER or GET PULLED OVER!!”

shared_text:
New Stage Players is at The Koffie Knechtion.
August 7 at 1:38 PM · South Sioux City, NE ·

New Stage Players announces special outdoor performances of “GODSPELL, JR.” August 28-30! The production will feature an all-adult cast and will take place at The Koffee Knechtion, 419 Golf Road in South Sioux City, Nebraska.

We are very excited to be able to partner with Music Theatre International to bring this junior version to life with an incredibly talented all-adult cast. Our team recognizes the past few months have been a challenge for live Theatre and are thrilled to be putting this production together, accepting the challenges of ensuring our cast’s safety during the rehearsal process as well as the safety of our audience for the performances.

Show times for “GODSPELL, JR.” are as follows:
Friday, 8/28 – 6:30pm
Saturday, 8/29 – 6:30pm
Sunday, 8/30 – 2:00pm

Tickets are $10 and will be available at the event. Patrons will be encouraged to bring chairs and/or blankets and are strongly encouraged to follow all COVID related guidelines.

It is a beautiful day outside and we cannot wait to see you all at 12:00 PM!!! Thank you again to the Tyson Fresh Meats Team and the Food Bank of Siouxland, Inc. for this incredible opportunity! 🤩🤩

YOUTUBE.COM
Nebraska P-EBT Program - Completing the Online Application

Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services
July 7 at 2:03 PM ·

The new Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) program provides benefits to families with children who received free and reduced school meals during the 2019-2020 school year. The program helps cover food costs for days schools were closed during the COVID-19 pandemic.

Currently families who are already participating in SNAP will have their benefits automatically placed on their EBT card. Families who are not currently participating in SNAP but have been determined eligible by their schools to receive free or reduced-priced lunches will need to apply for P-EBT through the P-EBT online application and will receive a specific “P-EBT" card.

Complete the Pandemic-EBT application here: https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

If you have questions, call the Economic Assistance Hotline at (800) 383-4278

The new Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) program provides benefits to families with children who received free and reduced school meals during the 2019-2020 school year. The program helps cover food costs for days schools were closed during the COVID-19 pandemic.

Currently families who are already participating in SNAP will have their benefits automatically placed on their EBT card. Families who are not currently participating in SNAP but have been determined eligible by their schools to receive free or reduced-priced lunches will need to apply for P-EBT through the P-EBT online application and will receive a specific “P-EBT" card.

Complete the Pandemic-EBT application here: https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

If you have questions, call the Economic Assistance Hotline at (800) 383-4278

If your child was on free or reduced lunch in Nebraska this last school year, you may be eligible for Pandemic EBT funds (similar to food stamps). Up to $281 per child. This program is not based on income, only on your child's free or reduced lunch status. Call the SNAP outreach hotline at 1-855-444-5556 today. It only takes 5 minutes to apply. Please have your child's student ID ready.

If you already receive SNAP benefits, you do not need to apply because you will automatically be enrolled. Please apply if you do not currently receive SNAP benefits.

shared_text:
Siouxland Freedom Park
May 11 at 4:31 PM ·

We have some exciting news to announce just two weeks before Memorial Day! We will soon be home to The Freedom Rock!

The concrete slab where the rock will be set has just been installed thanks to LiteForm and Nelson Commercial Construction!

On the docket for next week (hopefully) will be transporting the 21 ton rock to Siouxland Freedom Park from Frame Aligners in #SouthSiouxCity! (Thank you for donating the rock, Frame Aligners!!)

To transport the rock, Barnhart Crane will be donating the use of a large crane to pick up the rock and to place it at the park. B&B Rodgers will be the ones transporting this beauty!

A BIG THANK YOU to all involved in making this project happen! All of the services we needed to get this rock in place have been 100% DONATED! We live in a wonderful community! THANK YOU!!

We'll be posting updates on the rock's journey and when we can expect Ray Bubba Sorensen to paint the rock. Here's more information on our wonderful artist: https://www.thefreedomrock.com/

#freedomrock #murals #nebraska #veterans #memorial
